article.description: Nate Darling sank five 3-pointers and scored 21 points, Justyn Mutts added 17 points and nine rebounds and Delaware rolled to an 82-68 victory over UNC Wilmington on Saturday night.
article.headline: Darling leads Delaware past UNC Wilmington 82-68
article.linkText: Darling leads Delaware past UNC Wilmington 82-68
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- Nate Darling sank five 3-pointers and scored 21 points, Justyn Mutts added 17 points and nine rebounds and Delaware rolled to an 82-68 victory over UNC Wilmington on Saturday night. Darling had five assists for the Blue Hens (11-3). Kevin Anderson scored 11 points, while Ryan Allen and reserve Dylan Painter added 10 points apiece. Marten Linssen topped the Seahawks (5-9) with 15 points. Brian Tolefree had 12 points off the bench, while Shykeim Phillips contributed 10 points and four assists. Delaware shot 53% overall, 52% from 3-point range and made 14 of 15 free throws. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
